Question Name:
Concept:
Self-reported disability
Question Text:
Do you identify as a person with a disability?
Universe:
Note:
Source:
All respondents
This question allowed for respondents to self-identify as having a disability. Their re-
sponse cannot be compared to the disability status derived from the standardized set
of 41 Disability Screening Questions (DSQ). The DSQ module is based on the social
model of disability which focuses on social participation and one’s environment rather
than simply the health or medical condition itself.
